# Festibee Dashboard - Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js 13+ festival management admin dashboard with TypeScript and Tailwind CSS.

## Project Structure

### Core Files
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
- [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) - Root layout with sidebar navigation
- [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css) - Global styles
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind configuration

### Key Directories
- `app/` - Next.js 13+ app directory with pages and components
  - `festivals/` - Festival management pages and components
  - `artists/` - Artist management pages and components  
  - `places/` - Place management pages and components
  - `alarms/` - Alarm testing functionality
- `types/` - TypeScript type definitions
  - [types/festival.ts](mdc:types/festival.ts) - Festival, TimeTable, and related types
  - [types/place.ts](mdc:types/place.ts) - Place and Hall types
- `lib/` - Utility functions and API layer
  - [lib/api.ts](mdc:lib/api.ts) - Main API functions and HTTP client
  - [lib/utils.ts](mdc:lib/utils.ts) - Utility functions
- `components/` - Reusable UI components
  - `ui/` - Base UI components (button, input, etc.)
  - Shared components like PasswordModal

### Navigation Structure
The app has a sidebar navigation with 4 main sections:
1. **Manage Festivals** (`/festivals`) - CRUD operations for festivals
2. **Manage Artists** (`/artists`) - Artist management
3. **Manage Places** (`/places`) - Venue and hall management  
4. **Alarm Tests** (`/alarms`) - Testing functionality

### API Integration
- Backend API base URL: `https://darayo-festival.shop` (production) or `http://localhost:8080` (development)
- All API calls go through [lib/api.ts](mdc:lib/api.ts) with proper error handling and timeouts
- Password-protected operations for data modification

## File Naming Conventions
- Pages: `page.tsx` in feature directories
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `FestivalForm.tsx`)
- Types: kebab-case files with PascalCase exports
- API functions: camelCase